cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on learning distributed representations of social media users' writing style, which is a common topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural probabilistic language models (such as word2vec) and matrix factorization (such as GloVe) also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential applications of these embeddings in information retrieval (cs.IR) and social media analysis (cs.SI).
